Sure! Here's a sample marketing email using HTML and CSS to create an attractive layout:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Exclusive Gift Offer</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
       .container {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
       .header {
            text-align: center;
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
        }
       .header h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 24px;
        }
       .content {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
       .content p {
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333333;
        }
       .cta {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
       .cta button {
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: #ffffff;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 16px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
       .cta button:hover {
            background-color: #2980b9;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>Exclusive Gift Offer</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
            <p>Dear Valued Customer,</p>
            <p>We are excited to announce an exclusive gift reserved just for you! To claim your gift, please take a moment to complete the short survey below.</p>
            <p>Your feedback is invaluable to us, and we appreciate your time to help us serve you better.</p>
            <p>Thank you for your support!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cta">
            <button>Complete the Survey</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

This HTML and CSS code creates a simple and attractive email layout with a header, content section, and a call-to-action button. You can copy and paste this code into your email marketing platform to send it to your customers.

